Sidley Austin Appoints Nine Partners to Management, Executive Committees

-- B y   C u l l e n   W h e a t l e y
-- 
2011-09-26T18:19:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/sidley-austin-appoints-nine-partners-to-management-executive-committees.html
Sidley Austin LLP, the 11th-biggest
U.S. law firm, named six partners to its executive committee and
three to its management committee.  Brian J. Fahrney, Craig A. Griffith, Jennifer C. Hagle,
Matthew Sheridan, Susan A. Stone and Effie Vasilopoulos were
appointed to the executive committee, the Chicago-based firm
said today in a statement distributed by  Business Wire . Larry A. Barden, Mark D. Hopson and Larry J. Nyhan were placed on the
management committee, the firm said.  The 49-member executive committee exercises general
authority over the firmâ€™s affairs, according to the statement.
The 11-person management committee runs day-to-day activities.
Thomas A. Cole is chairman of the executive committee. Charles W. Douglas is chairman of the management committee.  Sidley Austin, with more than 1,500 attorneys, ranks 11th
in size by lawyers among U.S. law firms, according to the
National Law Journal, a trade publication.  To contact the reporter on this story:
